But as the audience is changing,
like the generation shifts,

00:53:16.850 --> 00:53:21.610
how do you see a change
in appreciation of music

00:53:21.610 --> 00:53:24.175
from people, from
the audience you get?

00:53:24.175 --> 00:53:26.550
Like as the generations are
becoming younger and younger.

00:53:32.677 --> 00:53:34.510
SAROD MAESTRO AMJAD ALI
KHAN: It's very rare

00:53:34.510 --> 00:53:38.690
to see people sitting
and performing nowadays.

00:53:38.690 --> 00:53:41.390
Everybody's dancing
and standing.

00:53:41.390 --> 00:53:43.980
So that is the basic difference.

00:53:43.980 --> 00:53:48.570
But we must protect
our tradition.

00:53:48.570 --> 00:53:50.155
We must protect our identity.

00:53:56.350 --> 00:53:58.740
So we'll have to
collectively make

00:53:58.740 --> 00:54:02.460
an effort to protect
our tradition.

00:54:02.460 --> 00:54:05.085
Every country's tradition,
every country's identity.

00:54:05.085 --> 00:54:06.580
It's very important.

00:54:06.580 --> 00:54:14.160
Because I feel that God
has given identity of music

00:54:14.160 --> 00:54:18.330
to every country through
a line of melody.

00:54:18.330 --> 00:54:20.550
In India, we have
so many states.

00:54:20.550 --> 00:54:23.580
Rajasthan, Gujarat, Punjab.

00:54:23.580 --> 00:54:26.540
Through a line of melody, you
can make out it's Gujarat.

00:54:26.540 --> 00:54:32.500
It is Rajasthan, or-- so that
is great blessings of God.

00:54:32.500 --> 00:54:36.600
And what music we have
this-- we don't read music.

00:54:36.600 --> 00:54:38.380
We don't write music.

00:54:38.380 --> 00:54:43.300
But we improvise and everything
is-- whatever we performed,

00:54:43.300 --> 00:54:44.570
we can't repeat.

00:54:44.570 --> 00:54:48.080
Only Google can show to the
world what we did today.

00:54:48.080 --> 00:54:51.120
But we can't give
identical concert.

00:54:51.120 --> 00:54:54.570
So it was especially meant
for all of you today.

00:54:54.570 --> 00:55:06.160
And so we must carry and
we must provide and promote

00:55:06.160 --> 00:55:07.910
our traditional art.

00:55:07.910 --> 00:55:12.180
Because life is
not entertainment.

00:55:12.180 --> 00:55:14.580
They are laughter
shows on the TVs.

00:55:14.580 --> 00:55:17.530
It's fine for few moments.

00:55:17.530 --> 00:55:21.350
But life is not just
entertainment or laughing

00:55:21.350 --> 00:55:22.600
shows.

00:55:22.600 --> 00:55:24.960
So a tradition, the
European music, the way

00:55:24.960 --> 00:55:29.620
they have preserved
Beethoven, Bach, Mozart.

00:55:29.620 --> 00:55:32.560
And I am also now
enjoying composing

00:55:32.560 --> 00:55:36.900
for orchestras and
Philharmonic orchestras.

00:55:36.900 --> 00:55:41.860
My work with the Scottish
Chamber Orchestra, [INAUDIBLE].

00:55:41.860 --> 00:55:44.120
So this is the way
that musically we

00:55:44.120 --> 00:55:45.890
can talk to each other.

00:55:45.890 --> 00:55:51.910
We can collectively
try to give the message

00:55:51.910 --> 00:55:55.090
that we are the same race.

00:55:55.090 --> 00:55:57.080
We love each other.

00:55:57.080 --> 00:55:58.710
If we can't help
each other, don't

00:55:58.710 --> 00:56:00.780
try to destroy each other.

00:56:00.780 --> 00:56:05.490
So I think we must
preserve our identity.

00:56:05.490 --> 00:56:08.970
And there are so many talented
among Amaan's and Ayaan's

00:56:08.970 --> 00:56:10.180
generation.

00:56:10.180 --> 00:56:12.320
There are so many
talented musicians

00:56:12.320 --> 00:56:14.720
in south India and north India.

00:56:14.720 --> 00:56:16.460
All over the world.

00:56:16.460 --> 00:56:21.470
So I think music has played
a very important role

00:56:21.470 --> 00:56:23.070
to connect the world.

00:56:23.070 --> 00:56:26.340
And music will continue
to connect the world

00:56:26.340 --> 00:56:32.061
through peaceful
music, appealing music.

